! Why one per plugin

Plugin-contributed leaders, pills, and entries already appear automatically in the live tables under ''Keys'', ''Pills'', and ''Entries'' — the protocol tags drive those cheat-sheets. The per-plugin help tiddler exists only for narrative context: a short table summarising what the plugin adds, with a story-river link to the plugin's full docs.

! Authoring a plugin help tiddler

```
title: $:/plugins/<author>/<plugin>/help
tags: $:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/help
ca-name: <plugin name>
ca-icon: <glyph>
ca-group: Plugin: <slug>
ca-order: 10
ca-hint: <one-line summary>

|!Adds |!Activation |
|`<key>` leader |drills into … |
|... |... |

→ Full docs: <$link to="$:/plugins/<author>/<plugin>/doc/overview"><plugin> overview</$link>
```

''→'' Authoring details: <$link to="$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/doc/protocol">doc/protocol</$link>
